</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">There is an agreed time (based on patient preference) for the medication to be taken. If the box is not opened at that time, there are up to eight further reminders (bleep), taking place at 5 min, 20 min, 30 min, 1 h, 2 h, 4 h, 6 h, and 8 h after the agreed time. Once the box has been opened, the reminders stop for that day.</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Medication box reminder (human voice) 4, 3, 2, and 1 d before the scheduled monthly follow-up visit.</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Adherence patterns based on patient interview, pill count from medication monitor box, and electronic data on dates and times of opening of the medication monitor box. Intensive management/DOT initiation and incentives as above.</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
